<glossary>
<definition id="fs-id1170902685108">
<term>angular momentum orbital quantum number (<emphasis effect="italics">l</emphasis>)</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1170902883846">quantum number associated with the orbital angular momentum of an electron in a hydrogen atom</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1170902754596">
<term>angular momentum projection quantum number (<emphasis effect="italics">m</emphasis>)</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1170903084175">quantum number associated with the <emphasis effect="italics">z</emphasis>-component of the orbital angular momentum of an electron in a hydrogen atom</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1170902691199">
<term>atomic orbital</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1170902691205">region in space that encloses a certain percentage (usually 90%) of the electron probability</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1170902867693">
<term>principal quantum number (<emphasis effect="italics">n</emphasis>)</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1170903125937">quantum number associated with the total energy of an electron in a hydrogen atom</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1170903125941">
<term>radial probability density function</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1170903125946">function use to determine the probability of a electron to be found in a spatial interval in <emphasis effect="italics">r</emphasis>
</meaning>
</definition>
</glossary>
